WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.833 --> 00:00:13.383
<i>Time of recording</i>
<i>is 10:49 on the 30th of December 2021.</i>

2
00:00:13.458 --> 00:00:16.128
<i>at an undisclosed safe house</i>
<i>in the Western Cape.</i>

3
00:00:16.708 --> 00:00:19.038
<i>Please. state your name for the record.</i>

4
00:00:19.125 --> 00:00:20.325
<i>Janet Nkosana.</i>

5
00:00:21.250 --> 00:00:23.750
<i>One more time.</i>
<i>From the beginning.</i>

6
00:00:28.333 --> 00:00:29.963
<i>It was before my time.</i>

7
00:00:30.750 --> 00:00:34.580
<i>but it all started when Julius Khumalo</i>
<i>approached Point of Grace</i>

8
00:00:34.666 --> 00:00:36.206
<i>regarding an adoption plan.</i>

9
00:00:36.291 --> 00:00:37.541
Breathe!

10
00:00:37.625 --> 00:00:39.825
-<i>He met someone from the agency…</i>
-Big push!

11
00:00:39.916 --> 00:00:43.416
<i>…and they agreed on a fee</i>
<i>in exchange for the baby…</i>

12
00:00:44.458 --> 00:00:45.458
<i>Phume.</i>

13
00:00:49.291 --> 00:00:51.211
Just cancel the deal. all right?

14
00:00:52.541 --> 00:00:55.001
No. I didn't cash it
so the money's still there.

15
00:00:55.541 --> 00:00:57.001
So call it off. okay?

16
00:00:58.916 --> 00:01:00.326
<i>Was Mrs. Khumalo aware?</i>

17
00:01:01.791 --> 00:01:03.081
<i>She was clueless.</i>

18
00:01:03.791 --> 00:01:05.831
<i>But it was too late.</i>

19
00:01:13.291 --> 00:01:18.581
You need to find the architect.
Find Lisbeth Molapo.

20
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:26.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

21
00:02:01.500 --> 00:02:03.250
Have you spoken
to Mama recently?

22
00:02:03.333 --> 00:02:05.043
I feel like she's avoiding me.

23
00:02:06.333 --> 00:02:09.383
I can't speak for your mom.
she's an adult and does what she wants.

24
00:02:12.083 --> 00:02:13.173
I just--

25
00:02:13.916 --> 00:02:18.626
Ever since Madam Nwabisa's disappearance.
I just feel like she also went AWOL…

26
00:02:19.416 --> 00:02:20.326
It's just odd.

27
00:02:22.375 --> 00:02:25.125
Well. then. why don't you just say
what you want to say?

28
00:02:27.250 --> 00:02:28.380
Okay.

29
00:02:28.958 --> 00:02:32.498
If you knew something
about Madam Nwabisa's disappearance.

30
00:02:32.583 --> 00:02:36.423
you would say something
to the police or me. right?

31
00:02:38.458 --> 00:02:39.958
If I knew something. yes.

32
00:03:14.041 --> 00:03:15.211
-Hi.
-Hi.

33
00:03:25.666 --> 00:03:28.126
Did. uh. Puleng tell you
that I also applied to Parkhurst?

34
00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:29.208
-Oh. yeah?
-I mean. yeah.

35
00:03:29.291 --> 00:03:31.131
Still waiting to hear
about the scholarship.

36
00:03:31.208 --> 00:03:33.498
but next year<i>.</i>
we could all be in the same school.

37
00:03:33.583 --> 00:03:34.673
-Hmm.
-How dope!

38
00:03:34.750 --> 00:03:35.830
Yeah. that's awesome.

39
00:03:35.916 --> 00:03:37.916
-So awesome.
-Come. I'll show you around.

40
00:04:02.416 --> 00:04:03.916
We painted it last year. but…

41
00:04:04.625 --> 00:04:08.875
we've kept it the same for 17 years.
just praying that this day will come.

42
00:04:11.500 --> 00:04:14.710
So. how much longer
are we supposed to stay here?

43
00:04:15.250 --> 00:04:18.130
As long as it takes
to put the major players behind bars.

44
00:04:18.625 --> 00:04:22.915
When are you going to look
into Matla Molapo. like I suggested?

45
00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.790
When you give us
something concrete to work with. Janet.

46
00:04:25.875 --> 00:04:29.285
Representing Point of Grace
is not enough to pursue a case.

47
00:04:31.625 --> 00:04:34.625
His role in this
is just so much bigger.

48
00:04:35.333 --> 00:04:37.833
He's just brilliant
at covering his tracks.

49
00:04:42.166 --> 00:04:44.376
Sooner or later. everyone slips up.

50
00:04:44.875 --> 00:04:45.955
When that happens.

51
00:04:46.541 --> 00:04:47.581
we'll be ready.

52
00:04:50.375 --> 00:04:52.495
Those are
from when you were born.

53
00:04:53.375 --> 00:04:57.375
Yeah. 16th of August.
in Cape Town at 3:00 p.m..

54
00:04:57.458 --> 00:05:00.168
with a full head of hair.

55
00:05:00.250 --> 00:05:01.420
Hello. reflux.

56
00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:09.710
Thank you for coming.

57
00:05:09.791 --> 00:05:12.711
I know that it's a very difficult time
for your family.

58
00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:15.670
Any update on Mrs. Bhele?

59
00:05:16.333 --> 00:05:18.383
Uh. we're holding up.

60
00:05:19.333 --> 00:05:21.173
and the police are doing their best.

61
00:05:22.916 --> 00:05:25.916
You know. I named you Phumelele
after your great-grandmother.

62
00:05:26.625 --> 00:05:29.245
She was a trendsetter.
Just like you.

63
00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:34.880
Am I a Zulu?

64
00:05:35.458 --> 00:05:36.748
Yes!

65
00:05:36.833 --> 00:05:39.003
Our family's from Amanzimtoti.

66
00:05:39.083 --> 00:05:40.423
Yep.

67
00:05:40.500 --> 00:05:41.750
And. um…

68
00:05:43.791 --> 00:05:45.961
-My biological father. is he--
-Uh. Siya…

69
00:05:46.541 --> 00:05:50.131
um. would you mind making
Fiks some of your special milkshake?

70
00:05:50.625 --> 00:05:51.915
Oh. okay.

71
00:05:58.958 --> 00:06:01.288
Does he think Mr. Khumalo is my father?

72
00:06:02.083 --> 00:06:03.923
Yeah. A tiny bit.

73
00:06:04.416 --> 00:06:05.536
And did you?

74
00:06:06.375 --> 00:06:08.625
I mean. like. before all the DNA stuff.

75
00:06:09.375 --> 00:06:12.245
I just thought we could
talk about everything today.

76
00:06:13.625 --> 00:06:15.915
Like. does he know about me?

77
00:06:19.916 --> 00:06:21.536
Are you gonna tell him?

78
00:06:22.125 --> 00:06:23.995
-It's complicated. Fikile.
-How?

79
00:06:24.083 --> 00:06:26.543
No. Fikile.
stop with the questions.

80
00:06:26.625 --> 00:06:29.165
No. seriously.
like. what more is there to hide?

81
00:06:29.958 --> 00:06:32.078
-Ma?
-Not now. Puleng.

82
00:06:35.500 --> 00:06:36.960
I'm sorry. Fikile.

83
00:06:38.291 --> 00:06:40.631
I don't think now is a good time
for us to talk about this.

84
00:06:40.708 --> 00:06:41.748
Then when is?

85
00:06:42.875 --> 00:06:44.955
Do you not think
I deserve to know the truth?

86
00:06:47.666 --> 00:06:48.996
This was pointless.

87
00:06:50.416 --> 00:06:51.536
Can we go home?

88
00:06:52.583 --> 00:06:53.833
You are at your home.

89
00:06:53.916 --> 00:06:55.416
You're home. my child.

90
00:06:57.291 --> 00:07:00.131
-Fiks. can we just--
-I'm sorry. Puleng. I can't.

91
00:07:13.291 --> 00:07:14.251
My child.

92
00:07:15.375 --> 00:07:16.745
Don't give up on her.

93
00:07:18.750 --> 00:07:21.080
Some things are hard
to discuss with children.

94
00:07:34.541 --> 00:07:35.541
Hello?

95
00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:40.500
Ma?

96
00:07:41.291 --> 00:07:43.331
-Mama. is that you?
-Let me see. let me see.

97
00:07:43.875 --> 00:07:46.125
Nwabisa? Nwabisa?

98
00:07:46.875 --> 00:07:48.575
Nwabi. is that you-- Nwabis--

99
00:07:54.375 --> 00:07:58.665
Oh. it was a disaster.
I don't get why she's being like this.

100
00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:00.750
I'm sure there's a good reason. Puleng.

101
00:08:00.833 --> 00:08:02.543
Yeah. well…

102
00:08:04.166 --> 00:08:06.326
Anyway. how's camping?

103
00:08:06.416 --> 00:08:07.706
Uh. it's okay.

104
00:08:08.583 --> 00:08:09.883
Just wish you were here with me.

105
00:08:09.958 --> 00:08:12.538
Yeah. no. Camping is the worst.

106
00:08:13.083 --> 00:08:16.333
Like. I don't get why anyone would go
somewhere just to be dirty all the time.

107
00:08:17.333 --> 00:08:19.333
I-- It's not that bad.

108
00:08:20.541 --> 00:08:22.081
Wade. can I call you back?

109
00:08:22.833 --> 00:08:23.923
Uh. o-okay.

110
00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:24.830
Cool.

111
00:08:26.208 --> 00:08:28.248
Cool. Miss you too.

112
00:08:28.958 --> 00:08:31.208
Wade. come get your breakfast.

113
00:08:42.375 --> 00:08:43.535
Someone did <i>kak</i> here!

114
00:08:44.458 --> 00:08:45.538
Bu…

115
00:08:47.791 --> 00:08:48.671
Fikile. I--

116
00:08:49.916 --> 00:08:52.286
-Hello. Aunty.
-Lunga. hello.

117
00:08:52.375 --> 00:08:54.955
-Hey!
-I-- How are you?

118
00:08:55.041 --> 00:08:57.381
Oh my goodness.
I completely forgot you were coming.

119
00:08:57.458 --> 00:08:58.708
Ah. no problem.

120
00:08:58.791 --> 00:09:00.461
-Mm-- Lunga!
-No.

121
00:09:01.083 --> 00:09:02.543
-No.
-Cuz. how are you?

122
00:09:03.166 --> 00:09:05.576
Siya. what are they feeding you?

123
00:09:05.666 --> 00:09:06.666
Oh!

124
00:09:06.750 --> 00:09:09.000
-Ah! You always have the best timing.

125
00:09:09.625 --> 00:09:12.285
You know what.
you guys are great for my ego.

126
00:09:12.375 --> 00:09:14.285
-Mm-hmm?
-Mm-hmm. mm-hmm.

127
00:09:14.375 --> 00:09:15.875
How long are you staying for?

128
00:09:15.958 --> 00:09:18.128
Uh. Lunga's staying with us
until he gets residence at--

129
00:09:18.208 --> 00:09:21.628
-Awesome!
-Yeah. Hey. I got everyone gifts.

130
00:09:21.708 --> 00:09:24.208
-But. hey. no peeking. all right?
-Okay.

131
00:09:24.291 --> 00:09:27.211
And I-- Ooh!
So. where is Mr. Julius?

132
00:09:28.708 --> 00:09:30.958
Um. I'll tell you everything.

133
00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:33.130
Or at least everything I know.

134
00:09:36.458 --> 00:09:38.378
We'll trace the call.

135
00:09:38.458 --> 00:09:39.328
Okay?

136
00:09:39.916 --> 00:09:41.496
But it could be from anyone.

137
00:09:43.583 --> 00:09:45.583
It's been three weeks now. detective.

138
00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:48.460
Should we be preparing for the worst?

139
00:09:50.166 --> 00:09:52.206
Any eventuality is possible.

140
00:09:53.291 --> 00:09:54.631
What I can promise you is

141
00:09:54.708 --> 00:09:56.878
that we are doing everything
we can to find her.

142
00:09:58.000 --> 00:09:59.210
I hope you find her.

143
00:10:00.416 --> 00:10:01.326
And arrest her.

144
00:10:02.791 --> 00:10:04.421
-No. Fikile.
-No. Dad.

145
00:10:05.041 --> 00:10:06.421
She did this.

146
00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:07.880
She lied to us.

147
00:10:07.958 --> 00:10:11.078
I mean. who could get into jail
and take her. honestly?

148
00:10:11.958 --> 00:10:15.288
She ran away and now we're stuck
to pick up the pieces.

149
00:10:15.375 --> 00:10:16.915
Don't talk like that. Fikile.

150
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:20.830
-We don't know the whole story.
-No. We don't know anything. do we?

151
00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:24.040
<i>Have you told Wade</i>
<i>about your smoochie with KB?</i>

152
00:10:24.125 --> 00:10:27.875
No. And I don't think I can. Zama.

153
00:10:27.958 --> 00:10:30.378
<i>Friend.</i>
<i>you know it's a bad idea not to.</i>

154
00:10:30.458 --> 00:10:33.418
<i>I mean. don't let this</i>
<i>bite you in the vajayjay later.</i>

155
00:10:33.916 --> 00:10:34.876
I know. I…

156
00:10:36.166 --> 00:10:39.996
-Um. Zama. I'll call you back later. okay?

157
00:10:40.083 --> 00:10:41.173
Hi.

158
00:10:45.333 --> 00:10:48.423
-I'm sorry about what happened earlier.
It's fine.

159
00:10:48.500 --> 00:10:49.960
How are you feeling?

160
00:10:50.833 --> 00:10:54.253
So. remember when you said
you'd help me find my father?

161
00:10:55.750 --> 00:11:00.170
I really need you to come through on that.
just you and me. no more lies.

162
00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:02.380
Please?

163
00:11:04.333 --> 00:11:05.883
As sisters?

164
00:11:10.041 --> 00:11:10.881
Yeah.

165
00:11:12.458 --> 00:11:13.578
Sisters.

166
00:11:20.208 --> 00:11:22.828
So. where do we start?

167
00:11:30.833 --> 00:11:32.083
No peeking. please.

168
00:11:32.583 --> 00:11:34.333
Mmm. No. This feels weird.

169
00:11:34.416 --> 00:11:36.416
-I'm gonna take it off.
-No. no. no.

170
00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:37.630
Patience is a virtue.

171
00:11:37.708 --> 00:11:40.538
Virtue? That's rich coming from you.

172
00:11:45.416 --> 00:11:46.826
This is incredible.

173
00:11:47.916 --> 00:11:51.166
-Wait. I didn't know you could cook.
-Mmm. I'm. uh…

174
00:11:52.458 --> 00:11:54.168
I'm full of surprises.

175
00:11:58.625 --> 00:12:01.955
-Sorry. we forgot your bisque.
-Just put it down and fuck off.

176
00:12:12.250 --> 00:12:13.130
Come on.

177
00:12:13.208 --> 00:12:15.078
A little lie and a caterer.

178
00:12:15.958 --> 00:12:18.498
Lot better than me
giving us food poisoning.

179
00:12:28.583 --> 00:12:29.583
Wendy?

180
00:12:32.916 --> 00:12:34.996
Okay. I have something to tell you.

181
00:12:35.625 --> 00:12:38.035
Remember that Future Leaders program?

182
00:12:38.958 --> 00:12:42.038
They kind of offered me a rotary exchange.

183
00:12:42.625 --> 00:12:44.535
But-- But that's amazing.

184
00:12:44.625 --> 00:12:45.535
In Spain.

185
00:12:46.791 --> 00:12:47.961
For six months.

186
00:12:54.083 --> 00:12:54.963
Good for you.

187
00:12:56.708 --> 00:12:58.788
We're not a thing. Remember?

188
00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:03.830
Okay. Chris. I'm sorry.
I should've given you a heads-up.

189
00:13:04.875 --> 00:13:07.285
I leave in the first week
of the new semester.

190
00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:12.206
I'm proud of you.

191
00:13:13.625 --> 00:13:15.125
For doing all the things.

192
00:13:19.083 --> 00:13:22.253
I just have to find someone else
to help me evade my taxes.

193
00:13:22.333 --> 00:13:23.753
"Avoid." Not "evade."

194
00:13:24.333 --> 00:13:25.463
Mm. same thing.

195
00:13:30.416 --> 00:13:31.626
Oh. shoot.

196
00:13:35.458 --> 00:13:37.078
Yes. yes. of course.

197
00:13:37.166 --> 00:13:41.036
Um. I-- I was just finishing up cleaning.
I was just… cleaning.

198
00:13:41.125 --> 00:13:42.325
Yeah. I'm on my way.

199
00:13:43.916 --> 00:13:46.166
-I have to go.

200
00:13:53.291 --> 00:13:55.631
Are you sure you're okay with all of this?

201
00:13:55.708 --> 00:13:56.748
Of course.

202
00:13:56.833 --> 00:13:59.633
I'm already planning
my. uh. summer in Spain.

203
00:14:01.333 --> 00:14:02.503
I'll see you later.

204
00:14:04.666 --> 00:14:05.666
Bye.

205
00:14:15.208 --> 00:14:20.078
-So. how are things?
-This place's better than the other place.

206
00:14:20.583 --> 00:14:21.463
Oof!

207
00:14:22.083 --> 00:14:23.503
-Ah. sorry.

208
00:14:25.208 --> 00:14:26.378
I'll be back.

209
00:14:26.458 --> 00:14:27.628
-Hi.
-Hi.

210
00:14:27.708 --> 00:14:30.708
Our records show there's
an outstanding payment from last month.

211
00:14:30.791 --> 00:14:32.831
I'd just like to check
when it will be settled.

212
00:14:32.916 --> 00:14:36.536
Yes. uh. sorry about that.
I'll get that done by the end of the week.

213
00:14:36.625 --> 00:14:39.785
Um. can you maybe just resend
the invoice to my email address?

214
00:14:40.333 --> 00:14:41.293
I'm good for it.

215
00:14:41.375 --> 00:14:42.745
I promise. Okay?

216
00:14:42.833 --> 00:14:46.713
Call the Underground Pub where I work.
speak to the manager. They'll tell you.

217
00:14:48.541 --> 00:14:49.381
Thank you.

218
00:14:49.458 --> 00:14:50.328
Thanks.

219
00:14:58.583 --> 00:15:01.083
We know about
the Point of Grace cheque book.

220
00:15:08.041 --> 00:15:11.541
I need you to know
that I did not take any of that money.

221
00:15:12.166 --> 00:15:13.416
Fikile…

222
00:15:14.833 --> 00:15:19.883
for the past 17 years.
in my heart. you've been my child.

223
00:15:21.166 --> 00:15:23.626
But I made a mistake before you were born.

224
00:15:24.500 --> 00:15:27.130
One that I'll have to take
responsibility for.

225
00:15:27.958 --> 00:15:30.958
I don't want to cause
any more pain for the two of you.

226
00:15:31.041 --> 00:15:32.421
I think you should go.

227
00:15:36.333 --> 00:15:37.923
That's okay. Mr. Khumalo.

228
00:15:39.250 --> 00:15:40.960
I'm not your problem anymore.

229
00:15:43.208 --> 00:15:44.668
Thanks for your time. though.

230
00:15:50.416 --> 00:15:53.826
Your father was…
Thandeka's client

231
00:15:53.916 --> 00:15:56.496
when she worked for Belmont Accounting.

232
00:16:01.750 --> 00:16:02.830
That's all I know.

233
00:16:03.541 --> 00:16:06.041
I didn't want to know any more details.

234
00:16:08.541 --> 00:16:09.381
Thank you.

235
00:16:16.750 --> 00:16:19.670
-This is harassment.
-We have a valid warrant. Mr. Molapo.

236
00:16:19.750 --> 00:16:22.330
-Your wife is now a person of interest.
-On what grounds?

237
00:16:27.083 --> 00:16:30.633
Cooperate. tell us where she is.
and you'll get leniency.

238
00:16:31.375 --> 00:16:32.575
Get out of my house.

239
00:16:47.791 --> 00:16:48.831
Hey. what's up?

240
00:16:48.916 --> 00:16:52.326
<i>It's official. Reece.</i>
<i>My academic appeal was denied.</i>

241
00:16:52.416 --> 00:16:53.576
Shit. Chris.

242
00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:56.540
Couldn't your parents do anything?

243
00:16:56.625 --> 00:16:58.075
<i>I don't think it registered.</i>

244
00:16:58.166 --> 00:17:00.666
<i>It's not like it really matters</i>
<i>to them anyway. so…</i>

245
00:17:01.166 --> 00:17:04.076
<i>I. on the other hand. might have</i>
<i>to move to a different country.</i>

246
00:17:04.583 --> 00:17:06.633
Don't be so dramatic.

247
00:17:06.708 --> 00:17:09.208
At least you'll have
your pick of the litter again.

248
00:17:09.875 --> 00:17:12.245
Thank you. Reece. Always such a comfort.

249
00:17:13.500 --> 00:17:17.580
<i>By the way. what ever happened</i>
<i>with you and Miss President of the World</i>

250
00:17:17.666 --> 00:17:19.456
<i>after your kiss at the matric ball?</i>

251
00:17:19.541 --> 00:17:23.001
<i>-Like. are you guys a thing now?</i>
-Wendy? No. I'd never seriously go there.

252
00:17:23.083 --> 00:17:25.173
It just shows you
that ice queens can't resist--

253
00:17:25.666 --> 00:17:27.456
-Wendy…
-Don't.

254
00:17:27.541 --> 00:17:29.671
-Wendy. come on.
-<i>Oh. shit. Busted!</i>

255
00:17:29.750 --> 00:17:31.000
I was just acting.

256
00:17:31.083 --> 00:17:33.083
We're not a real thing. remember?

257
00:17:34.250 --> 00:17:35.880
Mm. yeah. Sure.

258
00:17:37.375 --> 00:17:38.205
Wendy.

259
00:17:38.916 --> 00:17:39.956
Wendy. come on.

260
00:17:52.458 --> 00:17:53.288
Hi.

261
00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:54.830
Hi.

262
00:17:59.166 --> 00:18:00.126
Um…

263
00:18:00.208 --> 00:18:01.788
I can't stay too long.

264
00:18:01.875 --> 00:18:03.125
Yeah. me too.

265
00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:05.170
So?

266
00:18:07.458 --> 00:18:12.918
Looks like my mom could be involved
in this whole Nwabisa disappearance thing.

267
00:18:16.708 --> 00:18:18.458
And it looks like there's a…

268
00:18:19.250 --> 00:18:21.290
there's a witness willing to testify.

269
00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:24.210
I'm so sorry. KB.

270
00:18:26.791 --> 00:18:28.081
Are you okay. though?

271
00:18:33.458 --> 00:18:34.498
I feel like shit.

272
00:18:37.875 --> 00:18:38.745
And you?

273
00:18:38.833 --> 00:18:42.213
How've you been?
I haven't seen you since the matric ball.

274
00:18:44.291 --> 00:18:47.171
Well… same mess. different day.

275
00:18:48.625 --> 00:18:52.075
My best friend's in the middle of nowhere
living with her grandmother.

276
00:18:53.000 --> 00:18:54.880
I cheated on my boyfriend with my ex.

277
00:18:56.916 --> 00:18:58.876
You haven't told
anyone about the kiss. right?

278
00:18:58.958 --> 00:19:00.668
Come on. what do you take me for?

279
00:19:00.750 --> 00:19:03.290
Uh. the guy who wrote
a diss track about his hookups

280
00:19:03.375 --> 00:19:05.245
and performed it
in front of his high school?

281
00:19:05.333 --> 00:19:07.253
Okay. look. I won't tell anyone.

282
00:19:08.708 --> 00:19:10.998
but… I don't regret it.

283
00:19:11.958 --> 00:19:12.918
What?

284
00:19:13.666 --> 00:19:15.576
The kiss.

285
00:19:19.458 --> 00:19:20.458
Okay. well…

286
00:19:21.875 --> 00:19:22.955
I've gotta go.

287
00:19:25.041 --> 00:19:26.751
We can still talk. though. right?

288
00:19:27.875 --> 00:19:30.785
You know. this whole thing
with my mom has me offside. and…

289
00:19:32.250 --> 00:19:35.170
you're the only one who gets it.
besides Fiks.

290
00:19:35.833 --> 00:19:36.793
Yeah. of course.

291
00:19:39.333 --> 00:19:40.503
Cool.

292
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:11.041
Thai. Indian.
or you will have a burger?

293
00:20:12.208 --> 00:20:13.958
Um… Indian.

294
00:20:14.666 --> 00:20:15.576
Uh…

295
00:20:20.250 --> 00:20:21.540
Bhelekazi. my child.

296
00:20:23.250 --> 00:20:28.380
every family has a bad year.

297
00:20:30.750 --> 00:20:35.380
But this coming new year.

298
00:20:36.666 --> 00:20:39.326
uh. will be much better for us. okay?

299
00:20:40.833 --> 00:20:42.713
-Indian?
-Yeah.

300
00:20:51.791 --> 00:20:52.711
Hello?

301
00:20:55.416 --> 00:20:56.246
Hello?

302
00:20:58.666 --> 00:21:00.286
Mama?

303
00:21:01.750 --> 00:21:03.580
Mama. is that you?

304
00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:08.670
<i>Mama. if it's you.</i>
<i>please just say something.</i>

305
00:21:11.875 --> 00:21:12.785
<i>Mama?</i>

306
00:21:36.791 --> 00:21:38.881
I'm glad you made it back
for New Year's Eve.

307
00:21:38.958 --> 00:21:41.918
-For you. I'd travel back in time.

308
00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:43.000
Wow.

309
00:21:43.083 --> 00:21:45.003
-So. I got us champagne.
-Mmm.

310
00:21:45.083 --> 00:21:46.923
You want to do that thing
they do in the movies?

311
00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:49.710
Where they-- Where they--
Where they wrap it around. yeah.

312
00:21:49.791 --> 00:21:50.881
-Like this?
-Mm-hmm.

313
00:22:07.500 --> 00:22:11.170
Sam… it won't be forever. okay?

314
00:22:12.958 --> 00:22:14.378
If we play by the rules.

315
00:22:44.291 --> 00:22:46.791
I'm in! I'm in!
I'm going to Parkhurst!

316
00:22:46.875 --> 00:22:49.825
-Oh my goodness! Aw. Siya!
-Of course you are!

317
00:22:50.375 --> 00:22:52.375
-Congratulations.
-What's happening?

318
00:22:52.458 --> 00:22:55.038
-I'm going to Parkhurst.
-Oh my gosh. Siya!

319
00:23:20.625 --> 00:23:23.825
Welcome to another year at Parkhurst High.

320
00:23:29.125 --> 00:23:32.955
This year. we are adding
something special to Orientation Week.

321
00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:35.000
As you can see.

322
00:23:35.083 --> 00:23:40.213
each matriculant has
a grade eight mentee assigned to them.

323
00:23:40.291 --> 00:23:41.671
-Hey.

324
00:23:41.750 --> 00:23:42.920
Are you Siya Khumalo?

325
00:23:43.458 --> 00:23:44.288
Yeah. Why?

326
00:23:44.375 --> 00:23:46.285
You're Puleng and Fikile's brother. right?

327
00:23:46.375 --> 00:23:47.205
Yeah.

328
00:23:47.291 --> 00:23:50.381
Puleng's in my sister Leigh-Anne's year.
Come hang with us afterwards.

329
00:23:50.916 --> 00:23:51.956
Cool.

330
00:23:52.041 --> 00:23:53.711
…with the utmost respect.

331
00:23:53.791 --> 00:23:54.921
Hey.

332
00:23:55.000 --> 00:23:57.080
A warm welcome to you all.

333
00:24:01.208 --> 00:24:04.918
In other news.
I would like to take this opportunity

334
00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:07.210
to give a very special mention to…

335
00:24:08.250 --> 00:24:09.420
Wendy Dlamini.

336
00:24:13.791 --> 00:24:16.251
As of next week.
Miss Dlamini will be joining

337
00:24:16.333 --> 00:24:21.383
the Future Leaders
Foreign Exchange Program in Spain!

338
00:24:36.250 --> 00:24:37.710
Chris. Uh… Psst!

339
00:24:38.375 --> 00:24:39.325
Hi. Hi. there. Um…

340
00:24:40.833 --> 00:24:44.333
I-- I think you're in the wrong class.
This-- This is grade 11.

341
00:24:44.416 --> 00:24:46.286
I'm well aware of where I am.

342
00:24:46.375 --> 00:24:47.285
Thanks. Wade.

343
00:24:47.375 --> 00:24:49.665
Back to grade 11.

344
00:25:04.208 --> 00:25:05.248
What the hell?

345
00:25:08.291 --> 00:25:09.881
Dude. are you seeing this?

346
00:25:09.958 --> 00:25:11.708
Yeah. back at Parkhurst. huh?

347
00:25:15.416 --> 00:25:18.286
Sorry I'm late. ma'am.
I didn't realize you moved office.

348
00:25:18.375 --> 00:25:19.375
It's temporary.

349
00:25:20.458 --> 00:25:24.668
As we discussed at the end of last year.
your community service starts today.

350
00:25:26.166 --> 00:25:28.286
You will assist the cleaning staff.

351
00:25:29.375 --> 00:25:30.995
every day after school.

352
00:25:31.875 --> 00:25:34.125
Don't let me regret
my decision. Ms. van Rensburg.

353
00:25:34.208 --> 00:25:37.038
If I hear even a whisper
about you dealing at the school--

354
00:25:37.125 --> 00:25:41.075
Uh. got it. ma'am.
Shiny floors. no drug dealing. I promise.

355
00:25:42.458 --> 00:25:43.998
Thank you so. so much.

356
00:25:47.958 --> 00:25:50.038
Reece. remember.

357
00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:54.330
not a word to anyone
about Mr. Ferreira's antics.

358
00:26:07.041 --> 00:26:08.921
What can I help you with?

359
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:11.420
I'd like to talk
to one of your detectives.

360
00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:13.380
My name is Lisbeth Molapo.

361
00:26:20.750 --> 00:26:23.330
It's gonna be the longest year
of my fricking life.

362
00:26:23.416 --> 00:26:26.626
Bro. this year is already
fucked up for all of us.

363
00:26:27.833 --> 00:26:30.423
So we've got no choice
but to have each other's backs.

364
00:26:30.500 --> 00:26:32.330
-And make the best of it. yeah?
-Hey.

365
00:26:32.416 --> 00:26:33.456
Hey.

366
00:26:33.541 --> 00:26:35.001
Reece. what the fuck?

367
00:26:35.708 --> 00:26:38.918
How come Daniels forgives you for dealing
but makes me repeat grade 11?

368
00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:40.790
Do you want me to go to jail. Chris?

369
00:26:40.875 --> 00:26:44.325
The worst thing that's gonna happen to you
is you might actually learn something.

370
00:26:46.250 --> 00:26:47.080
You okay?

371
00:26:47.875 --> 00:26:49.035
We're here for you.

372
00:26:49.875 --> 00:26:51.285
Yeah. dude. talk to us. huh?

373
00:26:52.250 --> 00:26:54.630
-I mean. we all made it this far together.
-Yeah.

374
00:26:55.333 --> 00:26:57.673
KB's right. huh?

375
00:26:59.125 --> 00:27:01.415
We made it this far.
so no flaking this year.

376
00:27:01.500 --> 00:27:02.460
No flaking.

377
00:27:02.541 --> 00:27:03.831
No flaking.

378
00:27:03.916 --> 00:27:06.206
Mm-hmm. Tough times never last.

379
00:27:06.833 --> 00:27:08.503
Only tough people last. huh?

380
00:27:11.875 --> 00:27:14.165
-All right.

381
00:27:15.708 --> 00:27:18.458
I've gotta go scrub some toilets

382
00:27:18.541 --> 00:27:20.541
if I wanna make my shift
at the pub tonight.

383
00:27:20.625 --> 00:27:22.455
-See you guys later.
-Kill it.

384
00:27:23.000 --> 00:27:24.250
I've gotta go too.

385
00:27:24.791 --> 00:27:25.881
Grade 11 stuff.

386
00:27:27.083 --> 00:27:29.253
-Fun.
-Mm.

387
00:27:30.500 --> 00:27:32.380
-Shame. man.
-Nah. he'll be fine.

388
00:27:40.666 --> 00:27:41.536
Oh.

389
00:27:43.708 --> 00:27:45.668
So this is where you've been hiding.

390
00:27:48.458 --> 00:27:51.748
Come on. Wendy.
Would you tell you if you failed grade 11?

391
00:27:51.833 --> 00:27:52.923
Yeah. whatever.

392
00:27:54.375 --> 00:27:55.625
You could've told me.

393
00:27:55.708 --> 00:27:57.038
I would've helped you.

394
00:27:58.083 --> 00:27:59.043
I'm sorry.

395
00:28:00.166 --> 00:28:02.206
But you-- you told me you were leaving

396
00:28:02.291 --> 00:28:04.791
and I thought you were
embarrassed about us. so I panicked.

397
00:28:04.875 --> 00:28:07.955
Oh. and "ice queen"? That really hurt.

398
00:28:08.958 --> 00:28:09.788
I'm sorry.

399
00:28:10.541 --> 00:28:12.501
Let me make it up to you.

400
00:28:13.041 --> 00:28:14.881
I need to go set up for orientation.

401
00:28:14.958 --> 00:28:16.708
I-- I'll grab my bag
and I'll come help you.

402
00:28:16.791 --> 00:28:17.671
No. Chris.

403
00:28:18.250 --> 00:28:19.580
It's for matrics only.

404
00:28:25.500 --> 00:28:28.000
Let me understand. uh. you correctly.

405
00:28:28.583 --> 00:28:30.543
At the time of Phume's kidnapping.

406
00:28:30.625 --> 00:28:33.875
you had just closed
a highly-contested business deal

407
00:28:33.958 --> 00:28:35.958
requiring you to. uh. relocate.

408
00:28:37.083 --> 00:28:41.633
Except… you wrote a letter
that suggests otherwise.

409
00:28:43.208 --> 00:28:45.458
What this letter suggests.

410
00:28:45.541 --> 00:28:46.961
which is the truth.

411
00:28:47.791 --> 00:28:50.001
is that we had people lobbying against us.

412
00:28:50.708 --> 00:28:54.128
People who went to a lot of trouble
to ruin our deal.

413
00:28:56.208 --> 00:28:59.418
I left… to protect my family.

414
00:29:01.291 --> 00:29:02.581
So why come back now?

415
00:29:03.541 --> 00:29:04.581
To clear my name.

416
00:29:05.791 --> 00:29:06.881
For my son's sake.

417
00:29:07.875 --> 00:29:10.455
See. everything I've done.
I've done to protect him.

418
00:29:10.958 --> 00:29:14.248
That is why I'm here.
talking to you without a lawyer.

419
00:29:14.333 --> 00:29:16.333
Because…

420
00:29:16.416 --> 00:29:18.036
I've got nothing to hide.

421
00:29:19.125 --> 00:29:21.035
So I've looked
through my mom's old files

422
00:29:21.125 --> 00:29:22.745
from when she used to work at Belmont.

423
00:29:22.833 --> 00:29:24.833
and I didn't find anything
on her old clients.

424
00:29:26.041 --> 00:29:27.041
Okay.

425
00:29:28.041 --> 00:29:31.041
But why don't you maybe
come by the house again?

426
00:29:31.125 --> 00:29:33.875
-And you can ask her again--
-Uh… I can't.

427
00:29:34.375 --> 00:29:38.375
I'm sorry. but one mother
lying to me my entire life

428
00:29:38.458 --> 00:29:40.128
is all I can deal with right now.

429
00:29:42.250 --> 00:29:43.080
It's fine.

430
00:29:43.166 --> 00:29:46.746
I guess this is just another one
of my life's unsolved mysteries.

431
00:29:49.916 --> 00:29:51.166
Hey. Khumalo.

432
00:29:51.833 --> 00:29:53.633
I'll take that juice. thanks.

433
00:29:53.708 --> 00:29:55.418
Oh. it's for me and KB.

434
00:29:55.500 --> 00:29:57.630
Respect the grade 12s. Now come here.

435
00:29:57.708 --> 00:30:00.628
-He's Fikile Bhele's brother.
-So? Give me that juice.

436
00:30:00.708 --> 00:30:02.378
How about you get your own juice. bro?

437
00:30:02.458 --> 00:30:03.708
Hey! I'm talking to you.

438
00:30:03.791 --> 00:30:04.881
Yo. chill. man.

439
00:30:04.958 --> 00:30:05.958
-Like this?
-KB!

440
00:30:10.958 --> 00:30:12.708
What the hell? Leave him alone.

441
00:30:12.791 --> 00:30:14.711
-Or what?
-Or I'll knock your teeth out!

442
00:30:14.791 --> 00:30:16.671
-Hey. hey. hey!
-Guys. stop it!

443
00:30:16.750 --> 00:30:18.170
Get off me. Get off!

444
00:30:18.250 --> 00:30:20.130
Chris. you're not even allowed to be here.

445
00:30:20.208 --> 00:30:21.878
-Are you okay?
-What a pussy!

446
00:30:21.958 --> 00:30:22.878
Apologize to Siya

447
00:30:22.958 --> 00:30:24.788
or I'm taking you
straight to Principal Daniels.

448
00:30:24.875 --> 00:30:27.205
Go ahead. See how that works out for you.

449
00:30:34.083 --> 00:30:37.173
This is a sketch of a woman
seen in a taxi with baby Phume

450
00:30:37.250 --> 00:30:38.540
outside the hospital.

451
00:30:39.291 --> 00:30:42.581
Looks just like you
in this photo from 2003.

452
00:30:42.666 --> 00:30:43.626
Don't you agree?

453
00:30:45.291 --> 00:30:47.581
Could be me. could be someone else.

454
00:30:48.958 --> 00:30:52.918
Why don't you just bring in
the person that did the sketch

455
00:30:53.000 --> 00:30:55.500
and see if they can identify me
from a lineup?

456
00:30:55.583 --> 00:30:57.883
Coincidentally.
the witness died last week.

457
00:30:57.958 --> 00:30:58.958
Oh.

458
00:31:01.083 --> 00:31:02.213
That's unfortunate.

459
00:31:03.125 --> 00:31:04.915
Thanks for bringing Siya back home.

460
00:31:06.166 --> 00:31:06.996
It's all good.

461
00:31:08.083 --> 00:31:10.293
-Fiks wanted to come too. but--
-Yeah.

462
00:31:12.208 --> 00:31:15.378
Anyway. I--
I'm glad I got to see you too.

463
00:31:16.041 --> 00:31:17.961
Well. I'm gonna go back inside.

464
00:31:19.916 --> 00:31:21.496
-Puleng…

465
00:31:25.750 --> 00:31:29.420
I don't want us to be over.
and I know you don't want that either.

466
00:31:31.041 --> 00:31:32.921
KB. I'm-- I'm with Wade.

467
00:31:34.500 --> 00:31:35.420
I've moved on.

468
00:31:35.958 --> 00:31:36.878
Have you?

469
00:31:48.625 --> 00:31:49.535
How's Siya?

470
00:31:51.458 --> 00:31:52.288
Not great.

471
00:31:54.500 --> 00:31:56.630
It was very sweet of KB to bring him home.

472
00:31:56.708 --> 00:31:58.458
Yeah. they're pretty tight.

473
00:31:59.166 --> 00:32:01.126
KB is his mentor at school.

474
00:32:02.083 --> 00:32:03.963
You two seem very tight too.

475
00:32:05.500 --> 00:32:07.380
I thought Wade was in the picture now.

476
00:32:09.083 --> 00:32:10.963
You don't get to interrogate me. Ma.

477
00:32:12.541 --> 00:32:15.211
Especially since you don't want
to tell Fikile who her father is.

478
00:32:16.166 --> 00:32:20.126
-She doesn't want to come to this house.
-That is between Fikile and I.

479
00:32:20.833 --> 00:32:21.673
It's not.

480
00:32:23.000 --> 00:32:24.460
It's affecting all of us.

481
00:32:25.041 --> 00:32:27.671
First. you drive Dad away
with your secrets. and now Fikile too?

482
00:32:27.750 --> 00:32:29.250
He's the one who left me!

483
00:32:43.458 --> 00:32:45.168
Shortly after we got married.

484
00:32:46.750 --> 00:32:48.920
your father panicked and asked for space.

485
00:32:50.125 --> 00:32:53.745
I moved into a flat with a friend of mine
two months after my wedding.

486
00:32:54.833 --> 00:32:56.133
I was humiliated.

487
00:32:59.541 --> 00:33:00.541
So I partied.

488
00:33:01.750 --> 00:33:02.750
A lot.

489
00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:08.670
And then one night I went to a client's
farewell party at his art studio.

490
00:33:10.458 --> 00:33:11.458
Anthony Gabisa.

491
00:33:15.208 --> 00:33:16.328
He smelled good.

492
00:33:17.750 --> 00:33:20.330
And he gave me
the kind of attention that--

493
00:33:20.916 --> 00:33:21.876
that I needed.

494
00:33:24.875 --> 00:33:27.035
You're the one who wanted
to know the truth.

495
00:33:29.083 --> 00:33:30.963
A few days later. he left for LA.

496
00:33:32.791 --> 00:33:34.331
And your dad came back home.

497
00:33:37.250 --> 00:33:38.460
Everything was good.

498
00:33:41.541 --> 00:33:43.541
Until I found out that I was pregnant.

499
00:33:48.416 --> 00:33:49.626
-Is this him?

500
00:33:53.750 --> 00:33:54.920
Yes.

501
00:33:55.500 --> 00:33:57.790
Why don't you just tell Fikile
all of this. Ma?

502
00:33:58.375 --> 00:34:00.875
Because I don't want her
to think that she was a mistake.

503
00:34:04.333 --> 00:34:06.083
Now. I know you. Puleng.

504
00:34:07.375 --> 00:34:09.575
